6. **IS an authorization bypass**: Non-admin users can modify ACL configurations including adding themselves as admin

The CodeQL query name says "network-to-acl-file" - the finding is about unauthorized modification of ACL config (privilege escalation), not path traversal per se. But the data flow from network → file write is the core vulnerability.

